
msgid "Tarantool 2.5.1"
msgstr ""

msgid "Date: 2020-07-17 Tag: 2.5.1-1-g635f6e5"
msgstr ""

msgid "Overview"
msgstr "Общие сведения"

msgid "2.5.1 is the beta version of the 2.5 release series."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"This release introduces roughly 11 features and resolves 34 bugs since the "
"2.4.1 version. There may be bugs in less common areas. If you find any, feel"
" free to report an issue at `GitHub "
"<https://github.com/tarantool/tarantool/issues>`__."
msgstr ""

msgid "Notable changes are:"
msgstr ""

msgid "Synchronous replication (beta)."
msgstr ""

msgid "Allow an anonymous replica follow another anonymous replica."
msgstr ""

msgid "Fixed numerous crashes in Vinyl."
msgstr ""

msgid "Make implicit cast rules for assignment operation more strict in SQL."
msgstr ""

msgid "Updated curl version to 7.71."
msgstr ""

msgid "Compatibility"
msgstr "Совместимость"

msgid ""
"Tarantool 2.x is backward compatible with Tarantool 1.10.x in the binary "
"data layout, client-server protocol, and replication protocol."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Please `upgrade "
"<https://www.tarantool.io/en/doc/2.3/book/admin/upgrades/>`__ using the "
"``box.schema.upgrade()`` procedure to unlock all the new features of the 2.x"
" series."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"There are changes labeled with **[Breaking change]**. It means that the old "
"behavior was considered error-prone and therefore changed to protect users "
"from unintended mistakes. However, there is a little probability that "
"someone can lean on the old behavior, and this label is to bring attention "
"to the things that have been changed."
msgstr ""

msgid "Functionality added or changed"
msgstr "Изменения или добавления функциональности"

msgid "Core"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"**[Breaking change]** :doc:`/reference/reference_lua/box_session/push` "
"parameter ``sync`` is deprecated and deleted. It does not work anymore, and "
"a usage attempt leads to an error (gh-4689)."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"**[Breaking change]** Define new rules for implicit cast for assignment "
"operation in SQL (gh-3809). Read more: :ref:`sql-implicit_cast`."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Symbols of the Tarantool executable are not masked anymore. Some private "
"symbols may become visible and available for FFI and ``dlopen()`` + "
"``dlsym()`` (gh-2971)."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Add ability to set up logging early without configuring the ``box`` engine "
"(gh-689)."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"To retrieve information about memory usage, "
":doc:`/reference/reference_lua/box_info/memory` can be used (gh-4688)."
msgstr ""

msgid "Vinyl"
msgstr "Vinyl"

msgid ""
"``box.snapshot()`` now ignores throttling of the scheduler and forces the "
"dump process immediately (gh-3519)."
msgstr ""

msgid "SQL"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Use naming pattern “COLUMN_N” for automatically generated column’s names "
"(gh-3962). Read more: :ref:`sql_select_list`."
msgstr ""

msgid "Replication"
msgstr "Репликация"

msgid ""
"Add :doc:`/reference/reference_lua/box_info/replication_anon`. When called, "
"it lists anonymous replicas in the same format as ``box.info.replication``, "
"the only exception is that anonymous replicas are indexed by their uuid "
"strings (gh-4900)."
msgstr ""

msgid "Allow anonymous replicas to be followed by other ones (gh-4696)."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
":doc:`Synchronous replication </book/replication/repl_sync>` can be enabled "
"per-space using the ``is_sync`` space option (gh-4842)."
msgstr ""

msgid "Build"
msgstr ""

msgid "Add initial support for OpenBSD (gh-4967)."
msgstr ""

msgid "Misc"
msgstr "Разное"

msgid ""
"Don’t start the :ref:`‘example’ instance <creating-db-locally>` after "
"installing Tarantool (gh-4507)."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Before this release, the Tarantool package for Debian and Ubuntu "
"automatically enable and start the ‘example’ instance, which listens on the "
"TCP port 3301. Starting from this release, the instance file is installed to"
" ``/etc/tarantool/instances.available/example.lua``, but is not enabled by "
"default and not started anymore. One may perform the following actions to "
"enable and start it:"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"ln -s /etc/tarantool/instances.available/example.lua \\\n"
"    /etc/tarantool/instances.enabled/example.lua\n"
"systemctl start tarantool@example"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"The existing configuration will not be updated automatically at package "
"update, so manual actions are required to stop and disable the instance (if "
"it is not needed, of course):"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"systemctl stop tarantool@example\n"
"rm /etc/tarantool/instances.enabled/example.lua"
msgstr ""

